1
00:00:15,010 --> 00:00:16,860
They got scared.

2
00:00:18,020 --> 00:00:19,769
They fled two days ago,

3
00:00:19,770 --> 00:00:21,449
knowing we'd be looking into the Zhangs.

4
00:00:21,450 --> 00:00:22,659
Any way to check up

5
00:00:22,660 --> 00:00:24,020
on the Japanese

6
00:00:24,060 --> 00:00:25,250
living in Beijing?

7
00:00:25,900 --> 00:00:27,219
I don't deal with them much.

8
00:00:27,220 --> 00:00:28,450
Can't stand them.

9
00:00:28,820 --> 00:00:30,539
They're always sneaking around

10
00:00:30,540 --> 00:00:31,980
like they have something to hide.

11
00:00:32,050 --> 00:00:33,379
=Cases Between Us=
But I have informants

12
00:00:33,380 --> 00:00:34,459
in Liulichang Antique Market.

13
00:00:34,460 --> 00:00:35,939
They buy antiques for the Japanese.

14
00:00:35,940 --> 00:00:37,099
I'll have them

15
00:00:37,100 --> 00:00:38,369
=Episode 19=
ask around.

16
00:00:38,370 --> 00:00:39,689
Swing by my storeroom later

17
00:00:39,690 --> 00:00:41,100
and grab whatever you need.

18
00:00:42,780 --> 00:00:44,370
I owe you one. I'll pay you back.

19
00:00:45,900 --> 00:00:48,250
I've been waiting to hear that from you.

20
00:00:49,050 --> 00:00:51,739
I'll have Zhao Cai draw up an IOU.

21
00:00:51,740 --> 00:00:53,330
We'll put it in writing

22
00:00:53,370 --> 00:00:54,570
with thumbprints and all.

23
00:00:54,970 --> 00:00:56,219
Don't push your luck.

24
00:00:56,220 --> 00:00:57,459
Whose fault is that?

25
00:00:57,460 --> 00:00:59,569
You keep going on about paying me back.

26
00:00:59,570 --> 00:01:01,290
You think I'm hurting for little peanuts?

27
00:01:11,130 --> 00:01:12,620
What's going on?

28
00:01:15,840 --> 00:01:17,560
(Jingshi Police Department)

29
00:01:22,050 --> 00:01:23,370
Yang Dezhi, kill the engine.

30
00:01:31,210 --> 00:01:31,849
Cover me.

31
00:01:31,850 --> 00:01:32,730
Yes, sir.

32
00:02:01,900 --> 00:02:03,060
Everyone okay?

33
00:02:04,330 --> 00:02:05,450
Is it over?

34
00:02:07,770 --> 00:02:08,930
Are you all right?

35
00:02:10,980 --> 00:02:12,180
I'm fine.

36
00:02:12,810 --> 00:02:14,500
What could happen to me?

37
00:02:22,860 --> 00:02:24,620
Didn't leave a single one alive?

38
00:02:25,330 --> 00:02:26,650
Be my guest next time.

39
00:02:43,420 --> 00:02:45,220
That was way too close.

40
00:02:46,180 --> 00:02:48,020
They're playing for keeps.

41
00:02:55,370 --> 00:02:57,620
7.62 Mauser rounds. Military issue.

42
00:02:57,900 --> 00:02:59,300
Military issue?

43
00:03:11,460 --> 00:03:13,690
Left, right, turn.

44
00:03:56,900 --> 00:03:58,580
Broad daylight,

45
00:03:58,740 --> 00:04:01,340
and the Marshal storms in with troops.

46
00:04:01,930 --> 00:04:02,900
What?

47
00:04:03,050 --> 00:04:04,370
Are you here to ransack the place?

48
00:04:07,420 --> 00:04:10,460
I heard someone
tried to kill you yesterday.

49
00:04:11,770 --> 00:04:12,930
Where were you hit?

50
00:04:15,860 --> 00:04:17,940
Any idea who did it?

51
00:04:22,580 --> 00:04:24,820
You should come back to the army.

52
00:04:24,900 --> 00:04:26,019
I sent you to the school...

53
00:04:26,020 --> 00:04:27,459
To conquer the world,

54
00:04:27,460 --> 00:04:29,290
not chase petty criminals.

55
00:04:30,170 --> 00:04:32,140
I've heard that speech enough
to recite it.

56
00:04:32,970 --> 00:04:34,940
How many times do I have to say?

57
00:04:36,020 --> 00:04:37,850
Stay out of my business.

58
00:04:37,900 --> 00:04:40,140
I don't care about conquering the world.

59
00:04:42,090 --> 00:04:43,050
Fine.

60
00:04:43,620 --> 00:04:44,940
You don't.

61
00:04:45,410 --> 00:04:47,220
But they stay.

62
00:04:51,290 --> 00:04:53,619
Next time someone comes after you,

63
00:04:53,620 --> 00:04:55,359
it'll be me who loses face.

64
00:04:55,359 --> 00:04:57,120
Then why weren't you worried
about losing face

65
00:04:57,120 --> 00:04:58,650
when my mother died?

66
00:05:10,060 --> 00:05:11,650
Or

67
00:05:12,010 --> 00:05:13,480
is there something you were hiding?

68
00:05:13,480 --> 00:05:15,260
You insolent brat.

69
00:05:33,730 --> 00:05:35,850
Looks like I struck a nerve.

70
00:05:37,500 --> 00:05:38,850
It's hot out.

71
00:05:38,940 --> 00:05:40,380
You should head back.

72
00:05:46,940 --> 00:05:48,529
I won't make things difficult.

73
00:05:48,530 --> 00:05:50,260
Leave these four behind.

74
00:05:58,140 --> 00:05:58,969
Marshal,

75
00:05:58,970 --> 00:06:00,619
the Young Master is just hot-headed.

76
00:06:00,620 --> 00:06:01,969
Don't take it to heart.

77
00:06:01,970 --> 00:06:03,580
Find out which fool in Beijing

78
00:06:04,820 --> 00:06:07,900
dared to lay a finger

79
00:06:08,650 --> 00:06:10,259
on my son.

80
00:06:10,260 --> 00:06:11,020
Yes, Marshal.

81
00:06:11,530 --> 00:06:12,460
Close the door.

82
00:06:16,970 --> 00:06:18,020
Salute!

83
00:06:27,460 --> 00:06:28,610
What's this about?

84
00:06:30,290 --> 00:06:31,410
Let's be friends.

85
00:06:32,330 --> 00:06:33,580
Friends?

86
00:06:35,290 --> 00:06:37,260
Or did someone send you?

87
00:06:43,700 --> 00:06:46,940
We're all serving different masters.
No need to be at each other's throats.

88
00:06:51,730 --> 00:06:52,899
Do you know how much we've lost

89
00:06:52,900 --> 00:06:54,490
because of Yuan Hong?

90
00:06:55,620 --> 00:06:57,050
In the blood fluke case,

91
00:06:57,060 --> 00:06:59,189
the director went to prison,
drug development stopped,

92
00:06:59,189 --> 00:07:01,040
and the pharmaceutical factory
is bleeding money.

93
00:07:01,040 --> 00:07:02,259
Then the tram factory case.

94
00:07:02,260 --> 00:07:04,209
The factory director was arrested,

95
00:07:04,210 --> 00:07:06,820
the tram project is stalled indefinitely,

96
00:07:06,940 --> 00:07:10,019
and the shareholders lost everything.

97
00:07:10,020 --> 00:07:11,340
Then the Eight Alleys.

98
00:07:11,380 --> 00:07:14,139
The police cracked down
on trafficked women,

99
00:07:14,140 --> 00:07:15,619
and the brothels are nearly bankrupt.

100
00:07:15,620 --> 00:07:17,490
They can't even pay protection money.

101
00:07:17,580 --> 00:07:18,820
And now the Longevity Pills.

102
00:07:19,090 --> 00:07:22,340
What's so wrong
with selling a little medicine?

103
00:07:28,770 --> 00:07:31,220
If I don't do something,

104
00:07:31,580 --> 00:07:34,380
I'll be the one staring down
a gun barrel.

105
00:07:39,530 --> 00:07:41,050
Even so,

106
00:07:41,580 --> 00:07:43,490
that doesn't justify murder.

107
00:07:44,260 --> 00:07:46,380
When you beat a dog,
you look at who owns it first.

108
00:07:55,620 --> 00:07:56,650
True.

109
00:07:58,650 --> 00:08:00,849
But I didn't send the killers.

110
00:08:00,850 --> 00:08:01,970
Who did?

111
00:08:08,620 --> 00:08:10,900
The Longevity Pills operation

112
00:08:11,850 --> 00:08:15,340
is run by General Chen and the Japanese.

113
00:08:15,730 --> 00:08:16,619
We're just

114
00:08:16,620 --> 00:08:19,140
following orders.

115
00:08:19,530 --> 00:08:22,780
Those two brats
stepped on the tiger's tail.

116
00:08:23,090 --> 00:08:24,970
Who am I supposed to ask?

117
00:08:29,820 --> 00:08:31,379
Hand them over.

118
00:08:31,380 --> 00:08:32,890
Leave the rest to us.

119
00:08:33,260 --> 00:08:35,090
Your Young Master
already took care of them.

120
00:08:36,530 --> 00:08:38,540
The Marshal and General Chen

121
00:08:39,290 --> 00:08:41,809
may seem friendly,

122
00:08:41,810 --> 00:08:43,859
but two tigers can't share one mountain.

123
00:08:43,860 --> 00:08:46,420
One day they'll turn on each other.

124
00:08:46,450 --> 00:08:48,339
If Yuan Hong gets caught in the middle,

125
00:08:48,340 --> 00:08:50,130
he'll end up as cannon fodder.

126
00:08:51,410 --> 00:08:53,370
As for that Zhao boy,

127
00:08:54,650 --> 00:08:56,169
Zhao Chengru

128
00:08:56,170 --> 00:08:58,540
has spent his whole life playing it safe.

129
00:08:58,770 --> 00:09:00,060
Yet somehow

130
00:09:00,570 --> 00:09:01,499
he raised

131
00:09:01,500 --> 00:09:04,490
a troublemaker.

132
00:09:06,930 --> 00:09:08,420
He'd better watch himself.

133
00:09:20,080 --> 00:09:23,680
(Li Siqiao)

134
00:09:32,450 --> 00:09:34,540
Miss, have you seen this dog?

135
00:09:37,170 --> 00:09:38,449
Have you seen this dog?

136
00:09:38,450 --> 00:09:39,180
No.

137
00:09:39,690 --> 00:09:40,540
Mister,

138
00:09:40,690 --> 00:09:42,259
have you seen this dog?

139
00:09:42,260 --> 00:09:43,180
No.

140
00:09:43,500 --> 00:09:44,540
Maomao.

141
00:09:45,740 --> 00:09:46,730
Maomao.

142
00:09:48,380 --> 00:09:50,090
Have you seen this dog?

143
00:09:50,740 --> 00:09:51,660
No.

144
00:09:54,160 --> 00:09:55,680
(Lost Dog)

145
00:09:58,860 --> 00:09:59,940
Maomao!

146
00:10:01,020 --> 00:10:02,019
Maomao.

147
00:10:02,020 --> 00:10:03,019
Where have you gone?

148
00:10:03,020 --> 00:10:03,739
I was worried sick.

149
00:10:03,740 --> 00:10:05,460
Don't you ever run off like that again.

150
00:10:53,100 --> 00:10:54,300
Help!

151
00:11:07,640 --> 00:11:09,479
(Lost Dog)

152
00:11:09,480 --> 00:11:11,569
(No. 7, Dayu Alley)

153
00:11:11,570 --> 00:11:12,460
Jump.

154
00:11:12,620 --> 00:11:13,409
Jump.

155
00:11:13,410 --> 00:11:14,300
Jump.

156
00:11:15,810 --> 00:11:16,730
Good dog.

157
00:11:19,690 --> 00:11:21,139
You brought home another one?

158
00:11:21,140 --> 00:11:22,250
Belgian Malinois.

159
00:11:22,260 --> 00:11:23,499
Flown in from Belgium.

160
00:11:23,500 --> 00:11:24,460
Purebred.

161
00:11:25,980 --> 00:11:27,820
Purebred or not, it's still a dog.

162
00:11:29,050 --> 00:11:30,660
Show her what you can do. Drop the ball.

163
00:11:32,410 --> 00:11:33,300
Come on.

164
00:11:33,690 --> 00:11:34,940
What's one plus two?

165
00:11:36,930 --> 00:11:37,820
Good dog.

166
00:11:41,260 --> 00:11:42,770
What's the speed of light?

167
00:11:43,450 --> 00:11:46,499
Why don't you have it fetch the moon?
You've got too much time on your hands.

168
00:11:46,500 --> 00:11:47,580
Bite her.

169
00:11:48,930 --> 00:11:49,700
Woof!

170
00:11:53,150 --> 00:11:55,479
I baked a batch of egg tarts.
Take them to the police department.

171
00:11:55,479 --> 00:11:56,340
Why?

172
00:11:56,410 --> 00:11:57,689
Need Yuan Hong's help?

173
00:11:57,690 --> 00:11:59,739
After the Bai Lu case,
my article made the front page.

174
00:11:59,740 --> 00:12:01,049
The newspaper rewarded me.

175
00:12:01,050 --> 00:12:02,929
So I'm showing my gratitude
to Chief Yuan.

176
00:12:02,930 --> 00:12:03,899
Shouldn't you be

177
00:12:03,900 --> 00:12:05,580
thanking me instead?

178
00:12:06,310 --> 00:12:09,019
And on behalf of women who've been
oppressed and discriminated against,

179
00:12:09,020 --> 00:12:10,449
I'd also like to thank Chief Yuan.

180
00:12:10,450 --> 00:12:11,730
You?

181
00:12:11,930 --> 00:12:13,420
Who made you their representative?

182
00:12:13,620 --> 00:12:14,700
Are you taking them or not?

183
00:12:16,770 --> 00:12:18,340
Fine. I am.

184
00:12:19,290 --> 00:12:21,130
But egg tarts are too ordinary.

185
00:12:21,170 --> 00:12:22,820
I'll send him something

186
00:12:22,980 --> 00:12:25,820
he'll never forget.

187
00:12:27,740 --> 00:12:28,409
Mr. Zhao,

188
00:12:28,410 --> 00:12:30,219
are you taking up street vending

189
00:12:30,220 --> 00:12:32,060
at the police department?

190
00:12:32,530 --> 00:12:33,929
Chief Yuan thought

191
00:12:33,930 --> 00:12:35,259
everyone had been working too hard,

192
00:12:35,260 --> 00:12:36,019
so he asked me

193
00:12:36,020 --> 00:12:37,339
to bring you all tanghulu.

194
00:12:37,340 --> 00:12:38,739
Freshly coated in sugar. Come on.

195
00:12:38,740 --> 00:12:39,739
Seriously?

196
00:12:39,740 --> 00:12:41,169
Now that's a first.

197
00:12:41,170 --> 00:12:43,739
Chief Yuan always looks so stern.

198
00:12:43,740 --> 00:12:45,499
I didn't know he cared so much about us.

199
00:12:45,500 --> 00:12:46,169
If you ask me,

200
00:12:46,170 --> 00:12:47,049
he's the best chief

201
00:12:47,050 --> 00:12:48,739
among all divisions.

202
00:12:48,740 --> 00:12:49,379
Everyone,

203
00:12:49,380 --> 00:12:50,929
Chief Yuan's treating us to tanghulu.

204
00:12:50,930 --> 00:12:52,289
Let's thank him together.

205
00:12:52,290 --> 00:12:53,929
Thank you, Chief Yuan.

206
00:12:53,930 --> 00:12:54,929
Grab one.

207
00:12:54,930 --> 00:12:56,250
There's enough for everyone.

208
00:12:56,740 --> 00:12:57,770
Yang Dezhi.

209
00:12:58,140 --> 00:12:59,370
Where's Chief Yuan?

210
00:12:59,500 --> 00:13:00,289
At General Affairs.

211
00:13:00,290 --> 00:13:02,490
I think he's talking about new uniforms.

212
00:13:04,740 --> 00:13:06,739
The first three divisions
all got new uniforms. What?

213
00:13:06,740 --> 00:13:08,610
Are we your least favorite?

214
00:13:08,740 --> 00:13:10,130
Chief Yuan,

215
00:13:10,140 --> 00:13:11,379
calm down.

216
00:13:11,380 --> 00:13:12,460
Don't get worked up.

217
00:13:14,290 --> 00:13:16,660
You'll get your new uniforms.

218
00:13:17,020 --> 00:13:18,289
But headquarters

219
00:13:18,290 --> 00:13:19,490
hasn't released the funds.

220
00:13:20,290 --> 00:13:23,099
You'll have to bear with us
a little longer.

221
00:13:23,100 --> 00:13:24,730
You say that every month.

222
00:13:24,930 --> 00:13:25,979
When exactly?

223
00:13:25,980 --> 00:13:27,130
Give me a date.

224
00:13:27,200 --> 00:13:29,400
(Director Li, Director
of the General Affairs Division)

225
00:13:35,650 --> 00:13:36,820
Chief Yuan,

226
00:13:37,860 --> 00:13:39,370
did you offend

227
00:13:39,410 --> 00:13:41,490
someone from above?

228
00:13:42,050 --> 00:13:43,019
What do you mean?

229
00:13:43,020 --> 00:13:44,019
It's obvious

230
00:13:44,020 --> 00:13:45,890
the Division Four's been singled out.

231
00:13:46,020 --> 00:13:48,259
I'm just a small fish.

232
00:13:48,260 --> 00:13:49,809
There's nothing I can do.

233
00:13:49,810 --> 00:13:51,259
Please don't make this harder for me.

234
00:13:51,260 --> 00:13:52,259
Please.

235
00:13:52,260 --> 00:13:54,289
Secretary Xu controls the funding?

236
00:13:54,290 --> 00:13:56,010
No, he doesn't.

237
00:13:57,930 --> 00:14:00,809
But he's the man of the hour.

238
00:14:00,810 --> 00:14:03,449
Plenty of people are eager
to do his bidding.

239
00:14:03,450 --> 00:14:04,569
He's a powerful man.

240
00:14:04,570 --> 00:14:06,490
Why pick a fight with him?

241
00:14:14,900 --> 00:14:15,770
How about this?

242
00:14:15,860 --> 00:14:17,809
I'll submit another request.

243
00:14:17,810 --> 00:14:19,049
If that doesn't work,

244
00:14:19,050 --> 00:14:21,769
I'll see if we can recycle equipment
from the other divisions

245
00:14:21,770 --> 00:14:23,739
for some funding to get new uniforms.

246
00:14:23,740 --> 00:14:26,580
Give me some more time.

247
00:14:27,290 --> 00:14:28,379
One week.

248
00:14:28,380 --> 00:14:29,460
I'll do my best.

249
00:14:29,530 --> 00:14:30,490
You have to.

250
00:14:32,050 --> 00:14:32,970
Chief Yuan.

251
00:14:35,690 --> 00:14:37,569
I'd like to ask you a favor.

252
00:14:37,570 --> 00:14:39,580
Do you have any men with some free time?

253
00:14:41,050 --> 00:14:42,169
For what?

254
00:14:42,170 --> 00:14:43,099
Well,

255
00:14:43,100 --> 00:14:45,649
my daughter lost her dog.

256
00:14:45,650 --> 00:14:46,569
I was hoping

257
00:14:46,570 --> 00:14:49,060
someone could help find it.

258
00:14:50,170 --> 00:14:52,060
You want policemen looking for a dog?

259
00:14:52,530 --> 00:14:52,979
Yes,

260
00:14:52,980 --> 00:14:54,289
I know it's inappropriate,

261
00:14:54,290 --> 00:14:55,569
but I don't have a choice.

262
00:14:55,570 --> 00:14:56,979
Since the dog went missing,

263
00:14:56,980 --> 00:14:58,809
my daughter hasn't been
eating or sleeping.

264
00:14:58,810 --> 00:15:00,370
I was at my wit's end.

265
00:15:00,380 --> 00:15:01,169
Of course,

266
00:15:01,170 --> 00:15:01,619
I won't ask

267
00:15:01,620 --> 00:15:02,689
for free.

268
00:15:02,690 --> 00:15:03,339
I have

269
00:15:03,340 --> 00:15:05,739
a snuff bottle from the Jiaqing era.

270
00:15:05,740 --> 00:15:06,499
If you find the dog,

271
00:15:06,500 --> 00:15:08,820
you can have it.

272
00:15:09,290 --> 00:15:10,259
Does that snuff bottle

273
00:15:10,260 --> 00:15:12,090
happen to have a crack in it?

274
00:15:14,260 --> 00:15:15,700
You are?

275
00:15:16,260 --> 00:15:19,130
Special Investigative Consultant
of Division Four, Zhao Shaoshang.

276
00:15:19,690 --> 00:15:21,250
You're under Chief Yuan?

277
00:15:22,260 --> 00:15:23,250
His partner.

278
00:15:24,100 --> 00:15:25,460
A pleasure.

279
00:15:26,380 --> 00:15:27,649
Now that you mention it,

280
00:15:27,650 --> 00:15:29,259
I think it does have

281
00:15:29,260 --> 00:15:31,010
a crack.

282
00:15:31,530 --> 00:15:32,649
Looking for a dog, right?

283
00:15:32,650 --> 00:15:33,689
That's easy.

284
00:15:33,690 --> 00:15:34,649
Serving the public

285
00:15:34,650 --> 00:15:36,490
is the Division Four's honor.

286
00:15:36,810 --> 00:15:37,769
Much appreciated.

287
00:15:37,770 --> 00:15:38,619
Thank you.

288
00:15:38,620 --> 00:15:39,449
Chief Yuan,

289
00:15:39,450 --> 00:15:40,250
this way.

290
00:15:40,410 --> 00:15:41,490
Watch your step.

291
00:15:42,050 --> 00:15:42,769
Thanks.

292
00:15:42,770 --> 00:15:43,649
It's nothing.

293
00:15:43,650 --> 00:15:44,610
Thanks.

294
00:15:45,620 --> 00:15:46,569
You promised that.

295
00:15:46,570 --> 00:15:47,739
You're handling it yourself.

296
00:15:47,740 --> 00:15:49,250
Don't you want new uniforms?

297
00:15:49,250 --> 00:15:51,500
- Thanks for the treat, Chief Yuan.
- Thank you, Chief Yuan.

298
00:15:54,260 --> 00:15:56,060
You chew malt sugar every day.

299
00:15:56,100 --> 00:15:57,449
Some habits

300
00:15:57,450 --> 00:15:58,940
are better off broken.

301
00:16:02,770 --> 00:16:04,499
You say it's for our uniforms,

302
00:16:04,500 --> 00:16:06,660
but you're really after
that snuff bottle.

303
00:16:06,740 --> 00:16:08,420
I swear that's not it.

304
00:16:08,680 --> 00:16:10,820
Do you think so little of me?

305
00:16:24,450 --> 00:16:25,660
Watch the step.

306
00:16:30,260 --> 00:16:31,970
Why don't we sit on the sofa first?

307
00:16:32,140 --> 00:16:33,130
Director Li,

308
00:16:33,260 --> 00:16:35,770
may I take a look
at the snuff bottle first?

309
00:16:36,290 --> 00:16:37,180
Of course.

310
00:16:55,810 --> 00:16:56,809
Please wait for a moment.

311
00:16:56,810 --> 00:16:58,460
I'll get my daughter.

312
00:17:01,810 --> 00:17:03,060
That's it.

313
00:17:03,140 --> 00:17:04,530
Is that a national treasure?

314
00:17:04,820 --> 00:17:05,689
Well,

315
00:17:05,690 --> 00:17:07,379
not quite.

316
00:17:07,380 --> 00:17:09,579
But Emperor Daoguang once used it.

317
00:17:09,580 --> 00:17:11,390
Back when Lin Zexu destroyed
the opium at Humen,

318
00:17:11,390 --> 00:17:12,819
and Britain launched the Opium War,

319
00:17:12,820 --> 00:17:14,059
word reached the capital.

320
00:17:14,060 --> 00:17:16,440
The Emperor flew into a rage
and smashed something in the study.

321
00:17:16,440 --> 00:17:17,619
It was probably this.

322
00:17:17,620 --> 00:17:18,530
See?

323
00:17:18,860 --> 00:17:20,660
It was repaired.

324
00:17:21,300 --> 00:17:22,220
So?

325
00:17:22,900 --> 00:17:24,929
That gives it a story.

326
00:17:24,930 --> 00:17:26,290
Makes it worth collecting.

327
00:17:26,860 --> 00:17:28,729
It's not a proud story, though.

328
00:17:28,730 --> 00:17:30,249
What's worth collecting?

329
00:17:30,250 --> 00:17:31,539
Come on.

330
00:17:31,540 --> 00:17:33,490
Failure is what makes us stronger.

331
00:17:34,300 --> 00:17:35,380
Gentlemen,

332
00:17:35,900 --> 00:17:37,729
my apologies.

333
00:17:37,730 --> 00:17:39,489
My daughter found the dog.

334
00:17:39,490 --> 00:17:40,579
I was at the station

335
00:17:40,580 --> 00:17:42,009
all night,

336
00:17:42,010 --> 00:17:43,530
so I had no idea.

337
00:17:43,580 --> 00:17:45,050
I'm terribly sorry. My apologies.

338
00:17:45,060 --> 00:17:46,250
Get out!

339
00:17:46,490 --> 00:17:47,860
Get out!

340
00:17:49,340 --> 00:17:51,530
Why won't any of you believe me?

341
00:17:52,380 --> 00:17:53,579
Get out!

342
00:17:53,580 --> 00:17:55,299
- She's arguing with her mother.
- Get out!

343
00:17:55,300 --> 00:17:57,530
- She's always had quite a temper.
- Get out!

344
00:17:58,860 --> 00:18:01,120
Sorry. I need to go upstairs
and check on her.

345
00:18:11,650 --> 00:18:12,779
What happened?

346
00:18:12,780 --> 00:18:13,729
I don't know.

347
00:18:13,730 --> 00:18:15,539
She was perfectly fine.

348
00:18:15,540 --> 00:18:17,449
Keep her locked up.

349
00:18:17,450 --> 00:18:19,490
I've been working on a transfer
to Customs.

350
00:18:19,540 --> 00:18:20,819
We can't afford a family scandal.

351
00:18:20,820 --> 00:18:22,136
What scandal?

352
00:18:22,137 --> 00:18:23,689
She's your daughter.

353
00:18:23,690 --> 00:18:26,379
If people hear my daughter's gone mad,
how will that look?

354
00:18:26,380 --> 00:18:28,050
Aren't you aware of that?

355
00:18:38,280 --> 00:18:40,180
You're the one we're looking for, right?
Come here.

356
00:18:42,450 --> 00:18:43,489
Found you.

357
00:18:43,490 --> 00:18:45,530
That snuff bottle is mine now.

358
00:18:48,340 --> 00:18:49,250
Look.

359
00:18:52,540 --> 00:18:53,700
Is that blood?

360
00:18:55,640 --> 00:18:58,240
(End of Episode 19)

361
00:18:58,561 --> 00:19:00,201
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

362
00:19:00,201 --> 00:19:01,741
♪Troubled times
are but a laughing matter♪

363
00:19:01,741 --> 00:19:02,991
♪However, the world changes♪

364
00:19:02,991 --> 00:19:04,911
♪You'll still be by my side♪

365
00:19:04,911 --> 00:19:06,601
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

366
00:19:06,601 --> 00:19:08,171
♪Praise and blame come and go♪

367
00:19:08,171 --> 00:19:09,741
♪If this is my final chapter♪

368
00:19:09,741 --> 00:19:12,241
♪I'll solve this mystery with you♪
